Our data has 1523 observations and 53 variables; some of those variables are related to the assessment of several developmental domains in infants (age range: 0 - 71 months old) using the Ages & Stages Questionnaire, 3th Edition (ASQ-3), which is a developmental screening tool that pinpoints developmental progress in children between the ages of one month to 5.5 years.

For every subject we have at least one measurement and in average 1.89 assessments.

Developed by Matías Castillo Aguilar, Cristian Núñez Espinosa.
